text: Zdravko Čelar (; Rašinovac near Bosanski Petrovac, 15 September 1917 - Rakovac near Srbac, July 1942), was a Yugoslav partisan, posthumously awarded with Order of the People's Hero. Village Čib in Vojvodina was renamed Čelarevo in his honor after World War II. == Sources == * Category:1917 births Category:1942 deaths Category:Yugoslav Partisans members Category:Recipients of the Order of the People's Hero
title: Zdravko Čelar
